caption: Here was an excessively cute storefront outfitted with Desperado pictures in a trendy neighborhood  serving willfully authentic dishes. They definitely served me avocado dip, what they lacked with the appetizer they more than made up for with the margaritas. I enjoyed two lemon margaritas. They were so deliciously sweet that you didn't taste the tequila which made them all the more easy to drink. The only drawback is you can't take them off the premises. Beware they were just really well made they in fact contained enough alcohol to get you tipsy if you're a moderate drinker. All in all I would go back for the drinks and skip any extra sides. Also the ketchup and mustard bottles are in fact red and green salsa.
